  subhead="Your latest reel is a sixty-second sequence — raw 316 stainless tube arriving at the workshop, the mitre cut on the bandsaw, the joint set against a welding jig, the TIG torch touching down and a perfect bead flowing along the joint, grinding and polishing stages blurring past, and the final reveal: a mirror-finish stainless balustrade with glass-infill panels installed on a contemporary balcony overlooking a garden. Eighteen thousand views. An architect in North Oxford DMs: 'That balustrade is exactly what we need for a project — a first-floor terrace on a new-build. About 8 metres of 316 stainless with glass panels. Can you quote?' You are in the workshop. Without AI DMs, the message waits. With it, the architect confirms the run length, mounting surface, and handrail profile. Your lead is captured with project context and material specification."
